<TITLE> Suicide bomber kills 3 in NW Pakistan Swat valley </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Islamabad, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide bomber killed three people, including a policeman and two civilians, in an attack on a police checkpost in the restive Swat valley in northwest Pakistan on Sunday, the military said. "Three people were killed and one was wounded," a military official said, speaking on condition of anonymity. "It was a suicide bomber." The attack came a day after the military said it had cleared the Swat valley of most militants led by a firebrand pro-Taliban cleric, whose insurgent followers clashed with troops in the area for weeks
